The paper describes a programming challenge for swarm robotics, which involves developing algorithms for a group of robots to autonomously search for and collect resources. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as the robots must operate without human intervention and make decisions based on their environment. The challenge also involves system engineering (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA), as the algorithms must be flexible and adaptable to different resource distributions. Finally, the paper discusses the educational outcomes of the challenge, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing competencies in a specific field.
